ry of Boston. The New York Times called him the city’s leading cultural figure."},{"number":2,"category":"legacy","header":"He transcribed a medieval codex in Spain","body":"Trained as a medievalist, Whitehill earned a London doctorate on the Romanesque architecture of eleventh-century Spain and made the first full transcription of the Codex Calixtinus at Santiago de Compostela. The Spanish Civil War sent him home to American maritime history."},{"number":3,"category":"character","header":"He addressed a queen at the Bicentennial","body":"For the 1976 Bicentennial, Whitehill delivered a televised address on Boston’s history at the Old State House before Queen Elizabeth II. An Episcopalian Republican who kept a fifteen-thousand-volume library in a converted barn, he founded the journal The American Neptune."}],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"HD6604","marriage_number":1,"date_year":1930,"children_ids":["HD6609","HD6610"]}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD6195","link_text":"Edgar Weld King","display_label":"a fellow library director with a library named for him"}],"slug":"walter-muir-whitehill-1905"},"HD6609":{"id":"HD6609","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"generation_from_thomas":11},"bio":{"display_name":"Jane Revere Whitehill Rotch","first_name":"Jane Revere","last_name":"Rotch","married_names":[],"maiden_name":"Whitehill","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1781566185/193355367_05b8e228-308e-474a-b342-320a6fd2a6dc_kejj1a.jpg"},"parents":{"father_id":"I01850","mother_id":"HD6604"},"tags":[],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I01853","marriage_number":1,"children_ids":["HD6611"]}],"birth":{"year":1931,"date_precision":"year_only"},"death":{"year":2018,"date_precision":"year_only"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM919"},"slug":"jane-revere-rotch-1931"},"HD6610":{"id":"HD6610","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"is_talcott_descenda